1
00:00:49,007 --> 00:00:50,383
{\an8}Where is Mikoy?

2
00:00:50,467 --> 00:00:52,177
{\an8}Didn't he tell you?

3
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:54,054
{\an8}<i>He went to the office.</i>

4
00:00:58,391 --> 00:01:00,602
{\an8}<i>He didn't come to the office today?</i>

5
00:01:00,685 --> 00:01:05,065
{\an8}<i>Yes, ma'am. Mr. Pinagpala</i>
<i>has not yet reported to the office.</i>

6
00:01:13,823 --> 00:01:16,076
{\an8}Do you want
a flying kick to your face, huh?

7
00:01:17,118 --> 00:01:18,578
What am I saying?

8
00:01:21,998 --> 00:01:22,832
{\an8}Hey! Hey.

9
00:01:25,502 --> 00:01:26,586
{\an8}Mikoy!

10
00:01:27,295 --> 00:01:30,340
{\an8}I understand where
you're coming from, okay?

11
00:01:30,423 --> 00:01:33,426
{\an8}But what Alex and I
are telling you is true.

12
00:01:43,102 --> 00:01:45,897
{\an8}Even then, I still don't like that guy.

13
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:54,489
Wow, you're being a smartass!

14
00:01:58,493 --> 00:01:59,744
{\an8}You're being sarcastic, huh?

15
00:02:03,706 --> 00:02:05,583
{\an8}‪Calm down. Calm down!

16
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,051
Vicek!

17
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:01,472
And from the right corner,

18
00:03:01,556 --> 00:03:07,478
standing five foot ten but
six foot on his Tinder bio!

19
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:09,981
Weighing 155 pounds,

20
00:03:10,064 --> 00:03:15,028
the Pride of the Philippines!

21
00:03:15,111 --> 00:03:19,365
The Nation's top drinker
and the ultimate brother!

22
00:03:19,449 --> 00:03:22,201
Mikoy Pinagpala!

23
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:25,914
- Mikoy! Mikoy!
- Mikoy! Mikoy!

24
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:35,924
Mikoy?

25
00:03:47,018 --> 00:03:48,811
‪You can do it!

26
00:03:49,854 --> 00:03:53,107
‪Go, Mikoy! He's about to lose!

27
00:03:53,191 --> 00:03:57,028
‪-You can do it, Mikoy!
‪-Go!

28
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:00,740
‪Go!

29
00:04:01,824 --> 00:04:04,077
It's taking so long.

30
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:05,912
It's my second cup of coffee already.

31
00:04:07,121 --> 00:04:08,873
What the heck?
Is this going to end already?

32
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:11,084
- Looks like a tie!
- All right, I'll handle it.

33
00:04:12,293 --> 00:04:13,962
- Fighters!
- What now?

34
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:17,215
You know if you have
a nine-tailed beast inside you,

35
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:18,925
you have to unleash it now!

36
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:30,228
You're finished!

37
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:32,814
Mikoy! Mikoy!

38
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:39,946
You're finished!

39
00:04:40,029 --> 00:04:41,239
‪We're for Mikoy! We're for Mikoy!

40
00:04:41,322 --> 00:04:44,742
- Never give it up!
- We're for Mikoy!

41
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:49,080
‪-You're the man!
‪-Hey!

42
00:04:49,163 --> 00:04:51,332
What's going on here?
What's going on here, huh?

43
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:52,417
What is this?

44
00:04:55,044 --> 00:04:57,922
Bok, we're just… having some fun.

45
00:05:02,719 --> 00:05:04,137
So he's okay with Boss?

46
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:05,555
We already talked.

47
00:05:14,605 --> 00:05:17,483
- Hey, easy.
- Give me my 2,000.

48
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:19,402
- Mikoy, let's go.
- Hey!

49
00:05:19,485 --> 00:05:20,486
Alex.

50
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:24,324
Thanks, okay?

51
00:05:28,036 --> 00:05:29,787
Did I do something wrong?

52
00:05:33,082 --> 00:05:35,335
Next time you come to this office,

53
00:05:35,835 --> 00:05:39,422
don't walk in like it's
the grand premiere of your movie!

54
00:05:42,884 --> 00:05:44,761
Someone might recognize you.

55
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:50,224
Is that why the General removed me?

56
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:52,810
Because of my grand entrance?

57
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:55,188
Sorry about that.

58
00:05:55,271 --> 00:05:56,189
I got a little excited.

59
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:58,066
No.

60
00:06:05,073 --> 00:06:07,200
There are people who wants to shut down
what we're doing here.

61
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:08,201
Huh?

62
00:06:08,951 --> 00:06:09,911
How come?

63
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:13,956
Clearly, some people think
what we do isn't important.

64
00:06:14,582 --> 00:06:16,793
That's why General Norberto
is very worried.

65
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:19,712
And if something bad happens to you again,

66
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:22,840
he thinks that it will lead
to the demise of the agency.

67
00:06:22,924 --> 00:06:24,926
And they'll use that against us.

68
00:06:25,009 --> 00:06:26,219
Is that all?

69
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:27,553
Come on!

70
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:30,264
You can see I've got nine lives!

71
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,684
So I've got eight left!

72
00:06:34,268 --> 00:06:35,353
Right?

73
00:06:38,981 --> 00:06:39,857
Sorry.

74
00:06:40,858 --> 00:06:41,859
But…

75
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:44,278
that's not going to happen.

76
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:47,990
Why do you say that?

77
00:06:49,450 --> 00:06:51,285
Because you're always there.

78
00:06:53,412 --> 00:06:55,414
I know you won't leave me.

79
00:06:55,998 --> 00:06:57,875
And you'll always protect me.

80
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:02,046
Of course you will.

81
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:08,427
That's why I am not afraid,

82
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:10,346
as long as I'm with you.

83
00:07:21,149 --> 00:07:22,358
So, shall we go?

84
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,652
Sianong has been waiting
in the briefing room.

85
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:26,529
He might end up being "shorts" later.

86
00:07:27,905 --> 00:07:29,115
Let's go.

87
00:07:36,664 --> 00:07:39,625
You told your Dad I'm your boyfriend?

88
00:07:40,209 --> 00:07:43,379
And now you want me to meet him

89
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:44,672
and pretend to be your boyfriend?

90
00:07:44,755 --> 00:07:47,008
Hey, Angelito! Angelito, wait!

91
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:49,010
You're single anyway, right?

92
00:07:50,052 --> 00:07:51,762
Listen to me, Angelito. Wait! Wait!

93
00:07:51,846 --> 00:07:52,972
Just hear me out first.

94
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:56,058
- Okay, fine.
- Here's the thing.

95
00:07:56,142 --> 00:08:00,021
Ever since I leaked to you
that information about the Valtrovis,

96
00:08:00,104 --> 00:08:01,147
Dad's been furious.

97
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:04,984
To the point that he's questioning
my decision-making.

98
00:08:05,067 --> 00:08:06,527
So you lied?

99
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:10,823
I didn't know what excuse to make.

100
00:08:10,907 --> 00:08:12,283
So come on, please!

101
00:08:12,366 --> 00:08:13,618
What I don't get is,

102
00:08:13,701 --> 00:08:16,537
why do you have to use me
as an excuse as your boyfriend?

103
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:21,584
I was just hoping Dad would think

104
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:23,920
I'm just soft-hearted and blinded by love,

105
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:26,339
that's why I ended up
leaking the information.

106
00:08:26,422 --> 00:08:28,508
Please, Angelito! Please, Angelito!

107
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:31,844
Angelito! Wait! Wait!

108
00:08:31,928 --> 00:08:35,723
Angelito, if Dad finds out
that I lied to him again,

109
00:08:35,806 --> 00:08:39,060
he might suspend my privileges.

110
00:08:39,143 --> 00:08:41,521
Then I might be stuck at home,

111
00:08:41,604 --> 00:08:43,689
and I won't be able
to come to Campus anymore.

112
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:45,650
Please, help me out!

113
00:08:50,112 --> 00:08:51,405
I'll help you too.

114
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:53,324
I will never turn you down.

115
00:08:56,619 --> 00:08:59,330
The Sinigang Cartel making a move
against the Moravianos

116
00:08:59,413 --> 00:09:01,666
was their biggest mistake.

117
00:09:01,749 --> 00:09:03,084
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

118
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:06,546
After the incident at the Valtrovi party,

119
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:09,632
we believe Viktor moved immediately.

120
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:34,323
Yup.

121
00:09:34,824 --> 00:09:38,494
And we also believe
that those elements of the Cartel

122
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:40,413
have been integrated into the Moravianos.

123
00:09:40,496 --> 00:09:44,125
Just to make sure they won't go
against the Valtrovis.

124
00:09:57,305 --> 00:09:59,807
So why is Raphael's painting here?

125
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:00,725
Wow!

126
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:02,643
Cultured!

127
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:06,564
Just because we're simple
doesn't mean we have no culture!

128
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:14,322
But since we don't have her face,
we use Raphael's artwork.

129
00:10:26,709 --> 00:10:29,170
Wait, wait. Wait. She?

130
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:38,929
I just want to know how.

131
00:10:48,522 --> 00:10:50,358
That's what you think.

132
00:11:06,207 --> 00:11:07,583
And once we capture her,

133
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:12,171
we can extract information from her
that we can use against the Moravianos.

134
00:11:14,673 --> 00:11:17,176
Have you seen anyone
around Viktor and Donabel

135
00:11:17,676 --> 00:11:20,096
who could possibly be
the assassin La Fornarina?

136
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:35,611
No one.

137
00:11:37,530 --> 00:11:38,864
I didn't really notice anyone.

138
00:11:40,741 --> 00:11:44,829
But if I see anyone suspicious,
I'll report it.

139
00:11:45,788 --> 00:11:46,622
Okay.

140
00:11:46,705 --> 00:11:49,667
But one thing is for sure.
I'm absolutely certain about this.

141
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:52,753
This La Fornarina,
this world-class assassin,

142
00:11:52,837 --> 00:11:55,631
is very close to Donabel and Viktor.

143
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,599
Wait, isn't that kind of weird?

144
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:09,937
Getting that close to a killer?

145
00:12:40,718 --> 00:12:41,802
Let's go!

146
00:12:43,095 --> 00:12:44,263
Come on!

147
00:12:44,346 --> 00:12:45,556
Just relax.

148
00:12:47,558 --> 00:12:48,767
Relax?

149
00:12:49,268 --> 00:12:50,686
How can I relax?

150
00:12:50,769 --> 00:12:53,647
At any moment, I'm going to meet
your dad and lie to him.

151
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:57,443
What's so hard about that?

152
00:12:57,943 --> 00:13:00,654
Why, do you think I grew up
lying all the time?

153
00:13:01,697 --> 00:13:02,865
At the very least,

154
00:13:02,948 --> 00:13:06,577
I'm sure you've lied
once or twice in your life.

155
00:13:06,660 --> 00:13:09,038
No way! I don't lie!

156
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:12,166
Especially since they say if you lie,

157
00:13:12,249 --> 00:13:14,168
you'll get a lot of mouth sores.

158
00:13:15,544 --> 00:13:16,837
That's not true.

159
00:13:16,921 --> 00:13:19,465
Yes, it's true that lying is bad,

160
00:13:19,548 --> 00:13:22,092
but sometimes it can come in handy.

161
00:13:23,511 --> 00:13:25,888
Yes! Especially if you're a politician!

162
00:13:25,971 --> 00:13:27,515
Because as they say,

163
00:13:27,598 --> 00:13:28,933
"We lie every day because we're always

164
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:31,101
putting on a performance."

165
00:13:31,185 --> 00:13:35,231
Because the world only wants to see
the best version of ourselves,

166
00:13:35,314 --> 00:13:38,317
so we hide who we really are.

167
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:41,237
So, one way or another,

168
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:43,697
you've already lied.

169
00:13:46,116 --> 00:13:48,285
You're just making things harder.

170
00:13:48,369 --> 00:13:49,912
Here's what we'll do.

171
00:13:50,704 --> 00:13:52,373
If you don't want to lie,

172
00:13:53,207 --> 00:13:55,459
just use your imagination.

173
00:13:57,586 --> 00:14:02,007
I'm sure you have a crush
or someone you like.

174
00:14:02,841 --> 00:14:05,427
For example, Jennie from BLACKPINK.

175
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:09,473
Imagine a scenario where you two
are already together.

176
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:11,892
Imagine what you would say

177
00:14:11,976 --> 00:14:14,478
when she introduces you to her parents.

178
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:16,647
That's it!

179
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:19,233
Let's go!

180
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:21,151
Come on!

181
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:30,077
Is that Angelito?

182
00:14:50,055 --> 00:14:51,348
Hi, sweetheart!

183
00:15:00,983 --> 00:15:02,776
You arrived just in time.

184
00:15:03,652 --> 00:15:05,487
Come on. Let's have dinner?

185
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:06,947
Smells good!

186
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:09,283
But of course,
you smell better, my sweetheart.

187
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:15,623
Let's eat?

188
00:15:17,833 --> 00:15:18,876
Wow.

189
00:15:18,959 --> 00:15:21,629
Roasted chicken sisig?

190
00:15:40,147 --> 00:15:41,607
Boracay.

191
00:15:46,403 --> 00:15:47,446
Palawan?

192
00:15:54,119 --> 00:15:55,329
What's the problem with Mikoy?

193
00:16:14,348 --> 00:16:17,601
{\an8}If we want Mikoy to trust us,
we need to trust him first.

194
00:16:27,069 --> 00:16:28,070
That won't happen.

195
00:16:28,153 --> 00:16:30,322
What if it does, Bok?

196
00:16:39,206 --> 00:16:40,416
Okay, here.

197
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:43,919
What if Mikoy screws us over?

198
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,422
If he betrays us,

199
00:16:46,922 --> 00:16:48,549
I'll be the one to kill him myself.

200
00:16:52,428 --> 00:16:53,262
You said it.

201
00:17:06,942 --> 00:17:08,360
By the way, where's Mom?

202
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:11,822
She's asleep.

203
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:13,949
Do you want me to wake her up?

204
00:17:15,492 --> 00:17:16,910
No, it's okay.

205
00:17:17,411 --> 00:17:18,829
Let her rest for now.

206
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:20,581
Yes.

207
00:17:20,664 --> 00:17:22,750
Mom mentioned earlier…

208
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:27,337
that you decided
to go to the office today.

209
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:30,758
Yes.

210
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:33,010
I told her about it.

211
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:37,681
So, how was it?

212
00:17:41,268 --> 00:17:42,269
Was what?

213
00:17:43,437 --> 00:17:45,022
The office!

214
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:46,148
Right?

215
00:17:46,732 --> 00:17:47,816
It was fine.

216
00:17:48,942 --> 00:17:50,069
Just okay.

217
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:54,364
Did the people there miss you?

218
00:17:54,948 --> 00:17:58,077
Well, for sure,
since you've been gone for a while.

219
00:17:58,577 --> 00:17:59,828
Of course.

220
00:17:59,912 --> 00:18:01,038
Who else?

221
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:02,831
I'm definitely missable.

222
00:18:22,101 --> 00:18:24,895
Do you have any questions for Angelito?

223
00:18:28,816 --> 00:18:30,567
What did your father say

224
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:33,987
when you told him about the Valtrovis?

225
00:18:42,663 --> 00:18:45,124
At first, he was surprised.

226
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:48,585
But he told me

227
00:18:49,169 --> 00:18:51,213
not to tell anyone about it.

228
00:18:51,296 --> 00:18:55,008
That we should keep it a secret,
even from Mom and my brother.

229
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:59,346
Your father is a very smart man.

230
00:19:08,689 --> 00:19:13,026
Can I count on you
not to tell anyone else?

231
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:18,282
Yes.

232
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:20,284
You can count on me.

233
00:19:23,787 --> 00:19:25,914
So, let's have dinner, okay?

234
00:19:31,712 --> 00:19:34,840
I want you to tell me

235
00:19:34,923 --> 00:19:38,427
the love story
between you and my daughter, okay?

236
00:19:39,261 --> 00:19:40,512
Let's eat! Let's eat!

237
00:19:42,431 --> 00:19:43,765
See, Angelito?

238
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:45,934
You can do it!

239
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:51,857
You know,

240
00:19:52,774 --> 00:19:57,571
what I hate the most
are people who lie to me!

241
00:19:59,531 --> 00:20:02,826
So you know, and I know,

242
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:07,372
that you did not go to the office today!

243
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:10,542
Right?

244
00:20:11,126 --> 00:20:12,711
Because I called your office,

245
00:20:12,794 --> 00:20:18,175
and not a single one of them
saw your shadow at Vertex Global!

246
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:24,932
So, I am giving you one more chance

247
00:20:25,015 --> 00:20:27,267
for you to come clean

248
00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:29,603
and tell me the truth!

249
00:20:30,687 --> 00:20:34,524
Because you won't like
what I'm going to do.

250
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:41,740
Okay.

251
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:44,993
You're right.

252
00:20:46,828 --> 00:20:48,830
I didn't go to the office.

253
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:49,957
Gotcha!

254
00:20:51,667 --> 00:20:54,836
And if you didn't go to the office,
where did you go?!

255
00:20:59,883 --> 00:21:02,970
Is it true that you are FUBU
with my daughter?

256
00:21:09,101 --> 00:21:10,894
Did I say something wrong?

257
00:21:10,978 --> 00:21:12,521
What does that even mean?

258
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:14,022
True love, right?

259
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:16,817
Don't ask me what it means anymore.

260
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:18,652
And if it's not that,

261
00:21:19,736 --> 00:21:21,697
what do you have with Angelito?

262
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:37,337
Are you really serious about my daughter?

263
00:21:44,469 --> 00:21:46,054
Okay, fine. I'll admit it.

264
00:21:47,764 --> 00:21:49,141
I left the house…

265
00:21:50,142 --> 00:21:51,935
to meet my friends.

266
00:21:55,564 --> 00:21:57,983
And I met them because…

267
00:21:58,650 --> 00:21:59,484
What?

268
00:22:21,923 --> 00:22:24,176
Why didn't you just say so?

269
00:22:25,719 --> 00:22:28,805
Are your intentions pure with her?

270
00:22:29,765 --> 00:22:32,059
Yes, sir. It's true.

271
00:22:36,396 --> 00:22:37,731
How can you say that?

272
00:22:45,113 --> 00:22:46,740
Honestly,

273
00:22:47,908 --> 00:22:50,869
I don't know if I can find
the right words for this.

274
00:22:51,578 --> 00:22:54,456
But, I watched it in a teleserye.

275
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:56,166
It said there that

276
00:22:56,249 --> 00:22:59,586
when you find the person meant for you,

277
00:22:59,669 --> 00:23:02,089
your world starts to slow down,

278
00:23:02,172 --> 00:23:04,091
the surroundings start to glow,

279
00:23:04,174 --> 00:23:06,676
and the birds start singing.

280
00:23:09,096 --> 00:23:10,514
And honestly, sir,

281
00:23:10,597 --> 00:23:14,851
that's the cheesiest
and corniest thing I've ever heard.

282
00:23:14,935 --> 00:23:15,977
Until…

283
00:23:16,728 --> 00:23:18,188
I experienced it.

284
00:23:20,023 --> 00:23:21,817
When I met your daughter, Sofie.

285
00:23:24,736 --> 00:23:27,572
Not only did my world slow down,

286
00:23:27,656 --> 00:23:31,618
but time itself stopped.

287
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:36,873
Not only did the surroundings light up,

288
00:23:36,957 --> 00:23:40,001
but everything became more vivid.

289
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:43,922
And not only did the birds sing,

290
00:23:44,756 --> 00:23:49,511
but my heart started screaming.

291
00:23:50,178 --> 00:23:52,514
Please give me a chance.

292
00:24:12,617 --> 00:24:14,870
Sweetheart, I understand.

293
00:24:24,421 --> 00:24:29,009
Especially since the only faces
are mine and your mother's.

294
00:24:29,092 --> 00:24:33,430
And with us being here, we might
be making things worse for you.

295
00:24:33,513 --> 00:24:37,392
You might be remembering
that traumatic event again.

296
00:24:38,935 --> 00:24:39,936
Oh?

297
00:24:40,437 --> 00:24:41,605
That might be it.

298
00:24:51,156 --> 00:24:54,701
If you need space, just tell me.

299
00:24:55,410 --> 00:24:59,039
I can leave for a while,
if that's what you want.

300
00:24:59,122 --> 00:25:03,001
No! It's not like that, sweetheart, but…

301
00:25:03,710 --> 00:25:05,128
Sorry, I just didn't tell you because…

302
00:25:06,213 --> 00:25:07,505
I didn't want you to worry.

303
00:25:07,589 --> 00:25:10,383
Sweetheart, that made me worry even more.

304
00:25:11,343 --> 00:25:13,553
You could've just told me.

305
00:25:14,137 --> 00:25:17,265
If you wanted to hang out
with your friends,

306
00:25:17,349 --> 00:25:18,600
then go ahead.

307
00:25:19,768 --> 00:25:21,937
I promise, next time,
I'll ask for permission.

308
00:25:35,325 --> 00:25:37,911
Well, how was it?

309
00:25:42,624 --> 00:25:43,667
Which one?

310
00:25:44,167 --> 00:25:46,336
Your friends! Right?

311
00:25:48,421 --> 00:25:50,632
Did you enjoy it? What did you do?

312
00:25:51,758 --> 00:25:52,842
Well…

313
00:25:53,343 --> 00:25:54,469
It was fine.

314
00:25:54,552 --> 00:25:56,471
We just kept it chill.

315
00:25:56,554 --> 00:26:00,225
We didn't really enjoy much because
you weren't there.

316
00:26:05,188 --> 00:26:06,940
Okay, never mind.

317
00:26:07,607 --> 00:26:08,608
It's fine.

318
00:26:09,317 --> 00:26:12,112
Maybe you don't even want
to introduce me to them.

319
00:26:12,195 --> 00:26:14,990
No! Sweetheart, of course not!

320
00:26:15,073 --> 00:26:17,492
Are you kidding? Everyone would love you!

321
00:26:18,118 --> 00:26:19,369
- Really?
- Yes!

322
00:26:19,452 --> 00:26:20,954
- Really?
- I mean,

323
00:26:21,037 --> 00:26:22,998
I'm really in love with you!

324
00:26:23,081 --> 00:26:25,166
Really?

325
00:26:26,584 --> 00:26:27,419
Super, yes!

326
00:26:27,502 --> 00:26:29,129
How many friends do you have?

327
00:26:29,212 --> 00:26:31,631
Are there many? Are they all from Cebu?

328
00:26:32,132 --> 00:26:34,217
Well, actually, just two of them.

329
00:26:35,051 --> 00:26:36,720
They're from Manila.

330
00:26:36,803 --> 00:26:37,887
It's…

331
00:26:39,472 --> 00:26:40,682
Alex and Sianong.

332
00:26:48,273 --> 00:26:49,149
May I?

333
00:26:49,733 --> 00:26:51,192
Of course!

334
00:26:52,986 --> 00:26:53,903
Of course it's you.

335
00:26:57,365 --> 00:26:58,533
Of course!

336
00:27:01,328 --> 00:27:02,370
Perfect timing.

337
00:27:02,871 --> 00:27:04,205
Can it be tomorrow?

338
00:27:09,377 --> 00:27:10,754
Of course!

339
00:27:11,504 --> 00:27:12,505
Who else but you?

340
00:27:21,598 --> 00:27:23,350
Chiara the Valtrovi?!

341
00:27:31,608 --> 00:27:34,277
Actually, I'm worried about Mikoy.

342
00:27:34,361 --> 00:27:37,405
I didn't know if he might
be hiding something from me,

343
00:27:37,489 --> 00:27:40,700
and I want him to be part of my life,

344
00:27:40,784 --> 00:27:41,659
for good.

345
00:27:41,743 --> 00:27:44,913
I have a man who knows
about Norberto Ruiz.

346
00:27:47,123 --> 00:27:49,209
It looks like he was captured
by Valtrovi's.

